"{\"uid\": \"nytimes.com-athletic-5348707-2024-03-19-uswnt-olympic-roster-prediction-gold-cup\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Olympics With the NWSL season underway and the number of days until the Olympics growing smaller, it's time to start thinking about what the USWNT roster may look like for the first tournament under incoming head coach Emma Hayes.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21, \"end\": 25, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Women's_Soccer_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.264688739576973e-35, \"text\": \"NWSL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Women's_Soccer_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Women's_Soccer_League\"}, {\"begin\": 144, \"end\": 149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USWNT\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 222, \"end\": 232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Hayes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympics\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 8}, {\"ngram\": \"days\", \"from\": 57, \"to\": 61}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 68, \"to\": 80}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 103, \"to\": 107}, {\"ngram\": \"the first tournament\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 192}, {\"ngram\": \"incoming head coach\", \"from\": 199, \"to\": 218}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The three of us went off to independently pick our 18-player roster as things stand now, in mid-March.\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 337, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 250}, {\"ngram\": \"our 18-player roster\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 302}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 312}, {\"ngram\": \"mid\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 330}, {\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 331, \"to\": 336}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When we reconvened to compare notes, it turned out we had all selected the exact same 18 players.\", \"from\": 338, \"to\": 435, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"notes\", \"from\": 368, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"the exact same 18 players\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 434}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It feels like a sign.\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 457, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a sign\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement It would not make for terribly compelling reading if we all just patted each other on the back for our great roster-building acumen, though.\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 614, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"terribly compelling reading\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 522}, {\"ngram\": \"the back\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 567}, {\"ngram\": \"our great roster-building acumen\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 604}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We will give you our list, but also take stock of the player pool at a broader level and figure how locked-in some players seem and who is still refining their cases for inclusion.\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 795, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our list\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 640}, {\"ngram\": \"stock\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 661}, {\"ngram\": \"the player pool\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 680}, {\"ngram\": \"a broader level\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 699}, {\"ngram\": \"locked-in some players\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 737}, {\"ngram\": \"their cases\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 780}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 794}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Goalkeepers (2):Alyssa Naeher (Chicago Red Stars), Casey Murphy (NC Courage) Defenders (6):Naomi Girma (San Diego Wave), Tierna Davidson (Gotham FC), Emily Fox (Arsenal), Crystal Dunn (Gotham FC), Jenna Nighswonger (Gotham FC), Casey Krueger (Washington Spirit) Midfielders (5):Rose Lavelle (Gotham FC), Lindsey Horan (Lyon), Sam Coffey (Portland Thorns), Catarina Macario (Chelsea), Emily Sonnett (Gotham FC) Forwards (5): Sophia Smith (Portland Thorns), Mallory Swanson (Chicago Red Stars), Alex Morgan (SD Wave), Trinity Rodman (Washington Spirit), Jaedyn Shaw (SD Wave) Naomi Girma, Lindsey Horan, Rose Lavelle, Emily Fox, Alyssa Naeher This is the quintet that absolutely needs to be preserved in bubble wrap, ensured a good eight hours of sleep every night, and kept in good spirits between now and the Olympics.\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 1622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 830, \"end\": 847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago_Red_Stars\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chicago Red Stars\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago_Red_Stars\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago_Red_Stars\"}, {\"begin\": 850, \"end\": 862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Murphy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Casey Murphy\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Murphy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Murphy\"}, {\"begin\": 864, \"end\": 866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Carolina_Courage\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.81454296109377e-67, \"text\": \"NC\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Carolina_Courage\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Carolina_Courage\"}, {\"begin\": 867, \"end\": 874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courage\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6882333880653515e-14, \"text\": \"Courage\"